               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p>Thirteen different grants of land in <placeName>Maids Moreton</placeName>. 
                        1. <persName><forename>William</forename>, <surname type="patronymic">son of Reginald</surname></persName> grants to <persName><forename>Henry</forename>, <surname type="patronymic">son of Robert</surname></persName> and <persName><forename>Nicholaa</forename>, his wife</persName>, for 12 shillings 1 3/4 acres.
                        2. <persName><forename>Hericus</forename> <surname>Carnifex</surname> of <placeName type="person">Buckingham</placeName></persName> grants to <persName><forename>Henry</forename>, <surname type="patronymic">son of Robert</surname></persName> and <persName><forename>Nicholaa</forename>, his wife</persName>, an acre.
                        3. <persName><forename>William</forename>, <surname type="patronymic">son of Reginald</surname></persName>, grants for 11 shillings to <persName><forename>Henry</forename>, <surname type="patronymic">son of Robert</surname></persName> and <persName><forename>Nicholaa</forename>, his wife</persName> 1 1/2 acres.
                        4. <persName><forename>Rob.</forename> de <surname>Westmonasterio</surname></persName> grants for 21 marks to <persName><forename>Henry</forename>, <surname type="patronymic">son of Robert</surname></persName>, and <persName><forename>Nicholaa</forename>, his wife</persName> all his land and meadow.
                        5. <persName><forename>Elyas</forename> le <surname>Droys</surname></persName> and <persName><forename>Alina</forename>, his wife</persName> grant for 32s. 8d. to <persName><forename>Henry</forename>, <surname type="patronymic">son of Robert</surname></persName> three acres.
                        6. <persName><forename>Ric.</forename> le <surname>Frankelein</surname></persName> grants for 50s. to <persName><forename>Henry</forename>, <surname type="patronymic">son of Robert</surname></persName> 3 1/4 acres.
                        7. <persName><forename>Matthew</forename> de <surname>Strattone</surname>, archdeacon of <placeName type="archdeanery" role="archdeacon">Bucks.</placeName></persName>, grants to <persName><forename>Henry</forename>, <surname type="patronymic">son of Robert</surname></persName>, a virgate and a rent of 2s. from <persName><forename>Will.</forename> de <surname>Bayus</surname></persName>, both of which Matthew had from <persName><forename>Walter</forename> de <surname>Morton</surname></persName>.
                        8. <persName><forename>Walter</forename> de <surname>Morton</surname></persName> grants for 90s. to <persName><forename>Henry</forename>, son of Robert</persName>, 7 acres and pasture for 50 sheep.
                        9. <persName><forename>Will.</forename>, <surname type="patronymic">son of Reginald</surname></persName> grants for 40s. to <persName><forename>Henry</forename>, <surname type="patronymic">son of Robert</surname></persName>, 4 acres.
                        10. <persName><forename>Walter</forename> de <surname>Morton</surname></persName> grants for 10 marks to <persName><forename>Henry</forename>, <surname type="patronymic">son of Robert</surname></persName>, 7 acres.
                        11. <persName><forename>Walter</forename> de <surname>Morton</surname></persName> grants for 4 marks to <persName><forename>Henry</forename>, <surname type="patronymic">son of Robert</surname></persName>, 5 acres; rent a penny at Easter and 'unum capellum de rosa' on June 24.
                        12. <persName><forename>Walter</forename> de <surname>Morton</surname></persName> grants for 20s. to <persName><forename>Henry</forename>, <surname type="patronymic">son of Robert</surname></persName>, 2 acres.
                        13. <persName><forename>Will.</forename>, son of <persName><forename>William</forename> <surname>Carpentarius</surname> of <placeName role="person">Foxcot</placeName></persName></persName>, grants for 16s. to <persName><forename>Henry</forename>, <surname type="patronymic">son of Robert</surname></persName> 1 1/4 acres.
                     [No date.] <!--CHK, should we estimate the date, as same actors e.g. in Salter, Oseney nos. 784-784K where dates c. 1250--></p>
